
Abstract classes and Methods

=> Data abstraction is processing of hiding certain details
and showing only essential information to user

=> abstraction can be achieved with either abstract classes or interface

Abstract keyword = non-access modifier, used for classes and modifier

1. Abstract class: is a restricted class that cannot be used to create
objects (to access it, it must be inherited from another class).


2. Abstract method: can only be used in an abstract class, and it does
not have a body. The body is provided by the subclass (inherited from).

